You need a ntsc fix. It requires extracting the files from the ISO and replacing the xbe and renaming a file. Not hard to do.

I have the fix. Extract the files from the iso usin C-Xbox Tool. Then delete the default xbe and replace with the default xbe included with the fix. Then go into the Media folder and rename the "MoviesP" folder to "Movies". The use C-Xbox tool to remake the iso and burn. Works perfect.
